Global Climate Patterns: An Overview

Compilation of introductory summaries of all known climate patterns in order to stimulate further research endeavors
2015-2017
Authors
Affiliations

M.D. Grossi

University of Massachusetts Dartmouth

University of Miami

M. Monim

University of Massachusetts Dartmouth

A. Gangopadhyay, Ph.D.

University of Massachusetts Dartmouth

This evolved from a series of class projects in an Ocean Atmosphere Dynamcs class taught by Dr. Avijit Gangopadhyay at the University of Massachusetts Dartmouth in 2015. Student mini-reports were compiled into the first of what we envisioned to be a series of Technical Reports providing short overviews of all known climate patterns.

Additional research and outreach avenues are currently pending funding.

Technical Report

  • Grossi, M.D., M. Monim, A. Gangopadhyay (2017) Global Climate Patterns: An Overview of Arctic Oscillation, Pacific Decadal Oscillation, Pacific/North American Pattern, and El Niño/Southern Oscillation, University of Massachusetts Dartmouth School for Marine Science and Technology Technical Report SMAST-17-0401, doi:10.13140/RG.2.2.34586.44480.
